WorkoutDescription: WU: 15 Minutes of easy pedaling, work up into your Level 2 effort by end of 15 minute warm-up (POWER: Level 2 / HR: Zone 2 / PE: 4-5)  MS: Long ride with group or alone, focus most time in L2 ENDurance (POWER: Level 2 / HR: Zone 2 / PE: 4-5), as part of ride by completing 1 x 30 - 40 minutes TEMPO effort focusing on keeping watts in the TEMPO L3 Zone (POWER: Level 3 / HR: Zone 3 / PE: 5-6). Focus on "mixing" your spin cadence during the tempo. Terrian: Mixed. Cadence 85 - 105 (80 - 90 in Tempo) CD: 10 - 15 Minutes of easy pedaling
Relax. Watch TV. Take a walk. Stretch. Enjoy the day. IF you need to skip a workout this week, then skip either the Thursday easy ride or Friday's ride. That will reduce some hours.
CoachComments: WATCH your food intake today. Do not overeat. Eat a normal to small amount of food today. Your body will be craving tons of food today, but resist!

AthleteComments: *02/09/2016 Ralph Rogge: 10' Bike max L10/110rpm. 3x12: CP 37.5kg 8/10; LOB 35kg 8/10; PEC 27.5kg 8/10; LOR 40kg 8/10. 3x20 CR.*

WorkoutDescription: Make sure you are reading the PRE-ACTIVITY COMMENTS AS WELL!!! WU: 10 Minutes working Endurance (POWER: Level 2 / HR: Zone 2 / PE: 4-5) with 2 x 1 minute Fast Pedals to wake up legs MS: Today is simple, ride prescribed time in the ENDurance Zone (POWER: Level 2 / HR: Zone 2 / PE: 4-5) Vary cadence throughout ride and work on pedaling form. Practice “coming over the top” and “pulling through the bottom” of the pedal (pretend there is glass in shoes). Enjoy the day!! Terrain: Flat to Rolling; Cadence: 85 - 105.
CoachComments: This can be done with a group, just try to hit the target training levels! Do not eat before riding. Only black coffee. Take food for the road, protein packed sandwiches, etc. and begin eating at hour 2! This is so critical to teaching your body to burn fat at a higher rate of exercise. Do your best, but no bonking allowed! So if you start to bonk before the 2 hour mark, then you need to eat then. Don't worry, you'll get better at this as you continue on the plan.
AthleteComments: *03/09/2016 Ralph Rogge: Eine größere Runde. Ging gut. Auf dem Rückweg nach 2h bei Allensbach ein Käse(-eiweiß-)brot gegessen. Andreas Eschbach: Herr aller Dinge.*

WorkoutDescription: WU: 10 Minutes working into your ENDurance zone (POWER: Level 2 / HR: Zone 2 / PE: 4-5). Then complete 3 sets of 1 Minute fast pedals with 1 minute rest in-between to open up legs MS: Building Endurance today! Once warmed up, ride in your ENDURANCE zone (POWER: Level 2 / HR: Zone 2 / PE: 4-5) over flat to rolling terrain. Focus on staying relaxed on the bike and spinning circles while keeping cadence between 90-100. During the last hour of the ride complete one 30 minute TEMPO effort (POWER: Level 3 / HR: Zone 3 / PE: 5-6) using a gear that results in a cadence of 75-85. Complete the TEMPO effort as close to the end of the ride as possible while still allowing 10 minutes for warm down. WD: 10 Minutes of easy spinning
CoachComments: Do not eat before riding. Only black coffee. Take food for the road, protein packed sandwiches, etc. and begin eating at hour 2!

WorkoutDescription: This is a rest week. Take it easy and don't push it. Enjoy the time. Get in some stretching and maybe some yoga. Enjoy the time and let your body become refreshed. Your metabolism is really starting to ramp up and your body will think that you have another hard week of training coming. This means that you'll be hungry this week as your body tries to fuel up for the work that it thinks is coming. This week is critical to watch your food intake, so resist, resist the urge to over-eat. Drink plenty of water everytime you feel hungry. It's possible that you could lose 2-5lbs. of fat this week!

WorkoutDescription: Relax. Watch TV. Take a walk. Stretch. Enjoy the day.

You should be well rested today, so might as well get started on Monday and kick some butt! This will be a great week for you to push to the next level of fitness.  If you have to shorten this week, then skip Wednesdays and/or Thursdays workout. Or you can just do 2 hours on Sunday.  Go for it!!!!!!! This is one of my personal favorites. Makes you sooo strong!!! You can do it!. Such a great workout. Give it your best shot! WU: 15 minutes with effort at L2 Endurance (56-75% FTP, 69-83% HR, 2-3 RPE) MS: 6x1 minute, all out with effort at L6 Anaerobic Capacity (121-150% FTP, 130-150% HR, 7 RPE)! With 3 minute recoveries between each. 60 minutes riding at sweet spot, effort at Upper L3 Tempo/Lower L4 Threshold (88-93% FTP, 82-97% HR, 4 RPE). CD: 10 minutes with effort at L1 Active Recovery (55% FTP, 65% HR, 2 RPE)
CoachComments: 60 minutes at sweet spot is tough, don't underestimate this one! Perfect for stoking the metabolism though!

WorkoutDescription: WU: 10 Minutes working Endurance (POWER: Level 5 / HR: Zone 5 / PE: 7-8) with 2 x 1 minute Fast Pedals to wake up legs MS: For today’s ride find a course with 3-5 longer hill climbs. Start out in Level 2 - Endurance Zone (POWER: Level 2 / HR: Zone 2 / PE: 4-5) and with each climb put in a 3-5 minute effort in your VO2 Max Zone (POWER: Level 5 / HR: Zone 5 / PE: 7-8). After each effort, ride at low endurance for at least 5 mins to recover then back up to the prescribed endurance zone. Take each effort to the MAX! Terrain: Rolling to Hill Climbs; Cadence: 85 - 105. WD: 10 minutes
